The U.S. military carried out a drone strike in Afghanistan on August 29 that killed 10 people including 7 children, citing intelligence about a car with explosive material inside. CNN investigated the U.S. military claims about the strike, conducting interviews ‘that paint a very different version of events.’

U.S. Gen. Kenneth McKenzie Jr. has since apologized for the civilian deaths, stating ‘we now assess that it is unlikely the vehicle and those who died were associated with ISIS-K’

#dronevideo #military #dronestrike #afghanistan #investigation

node.title: Investigating a U.S. Drone Strike in Afghanistan

node.text:
European Union scientists say the ozone hole over Antarctica has grown to among its largest size in the last 15 years, surpassing the continent's size, per the Associated Press.⁠
⁠
'Forecasts show that this year's hole has evolved into a rather larger than usual one,' said Vincent-Henri Peuch, the head of EU monitoring group the Copernicus Atmosphere Monitoring Service. Last year's ozone hole also started consistent with typical growth rates but hastened into one of the longest-lasting ones on record, added Peuch, per AP. He said that this ozone hole is 'quite big' and potentially 'deep.'⁠
⁠
The ozone protects living creatures on the Earth's surface from high-energy radiation by absorbing ultraviolet light coming from the sun.⁠
⁠
Experts say though there are signs the ozone layer is recovering, it will take into the 2060s to entirely rid it of depleting substances from sources like refrigerants and spray cans, per NBC News.⁠
⁠
⁠
#climatechange #antarctica #eu #ozone #environment
